    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">anukleat</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001405"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Anucleate is a quality describing a cell lacking a nucleus, manifesting as a subtype of nucleate deficiency</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'anucleate' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'nucleate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001405.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">NucleateQuality(x) ← Anucleate(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;anucleate&apos; then x is a &apos;nucleate quality&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;anucleate&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/BehavioralQuality">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/OrganismalQuality"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Verhaltensqualität</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">behavioral quality</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000186"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Behavioral quality denotes the aggregate of responses, reactions, or movements exhibited in a specific context</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'behavioral quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'organismal quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000186.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">OrganismalQuality(x) ← BehavioralQuality(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;behavioral quality&apos; then x is a &apos;organismal quality&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;behavioral quality&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/FemaleReceptivity">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Receptivity"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">female receptivity</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">weibliche Empfänglichkeit</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001720"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Female receptivity reflects the extent of a female's responsiveness to male advances</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'female receptivity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'receptivity'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001720.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Receptivity(x) ← FemaleReceptivity(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;female receptivity&apos; then x is a &apos;receptivity&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;female receptivity&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/SemiFertile">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Fertility"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">halbfruchtbar</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">semi-fertile</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001767"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Semi-fertile quality reflects partial fertility</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'semi-fertile' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'fertility'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001767.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Fertility(x) ← SemiFertile(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;semi-fertile&apos; then x is a &apos;fertility&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;semi-fertile&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/IntactMale">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Male"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">intact male</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">intakter Mann</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002366"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Intact male quality indicates possessing complete, unaltered reproductive organs</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'intact male' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'male'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002366.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Male(x) ← IntactMale(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;intact male&apos; then x is a &apos;male&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;intact male&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Prepupal">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Maturity"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Vorpuppe</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prepupal</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001188"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Prepupal quality describes being in an inactive development stage between larval and pupal phases</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'prepupal' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'maturity'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001188.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Maturity(x) ← Prepupal(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;prepupal&apos; then x is a &apos;maturity&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;prepupal&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Neonatal">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Maturity"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">neonatal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">neonatal</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002206"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Neonatal maturity quality signifies the period surrounding birth, immediately before or after</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'neonatal' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'maturity'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002206.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Maturity(x) ← Neonatal(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;neonatal&apos; then x is a &apos;maturity&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;neonatal&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Diandrous">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/PhenotypicSex"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">diandrous</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">zweidamig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040050"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Diandrous is a quality defines a plant structure in which flowers contain two stamens</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'diandrous' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'phenotypic sex'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040050.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">PhenotypicSex(x) ← Diandrous(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;diandrous&apos; then x is a &apos;phenotypic sex&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;diandrous&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/MaleSemiFertile">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/SemiFertile"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">male semi-fertile</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">männlich halbfruchtbar</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001761"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Male semi-fertile quality indicates a male’s partial capability for reproduction</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'male semi-fertile' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'semi-fertile'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001761.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">SemiFertile(x) ← MaleSemiFertile(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;male semi-fertile&apos; then x is a &apos;semi fertile&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;male semi-fertile&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/ProtandrousHermaphroditism">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Protandrous"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">protandrischer Hermaphroditismus</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">protandrous hermaphroditism</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040055"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Protandrous hermaphroditism involves organisms starting as male and becoming hermaphroditic over time</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'protandrous hermaphroditism' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'protandrous'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040055.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Protandrous(x) ← ProtandrousHermaphroditism(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;protandrous hermaphroditism&apos; then x is a &apos;protandrous&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;protandrous hermaphroditism&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/ReproductiveQuality">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/OrganismalQuality"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">reproductive quality</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">reproduktive Qualität</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001434"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Reproductive quality encapsulates the ability to produce offspring or new life forms</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'reproductive quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'organismal quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001434.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">OrganismalQuality(x) ← ReproductiveQuality(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;reproductive quality&apos; then x is a &apos;organismal quality&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;reproductive quality&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/MaleWithDsd">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/PhenotypicSex"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">male with dsd</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">männlich mit dsd</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040049"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Male with dsd quality pertains to males having ambiguous or atypical congenital development of reproductive systems</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'male with dsd' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'phenotypic sex'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040049.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">PhenotypicSex(x) ← MaleWithDsd(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;male with dsd&apos; then x is a &apos;phenotypic sex&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;male with dsd&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Arboreal">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/OrganismalQuality"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">arboreal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">baumlebend</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0095004"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Arboreal is a quality characterizes organisms adapted for life within trees through specific morphological and physiological traits</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'arboreal' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'organismal quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0095004.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">OrganismalQuality(x) ← Arboreal(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;arboreal&apos; then x is a &apos;organismal quality&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;arboreal&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/BroodSize">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/BroodQuality"/>
