    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Phenotypic sex quality pertains to the physical expression of sexual characteristics</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'phenotypic sex' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'biological sex'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001894.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">BiologicalSex(x) ← PhenotypicSex(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;phenotypic sex&apos; then x is a &apos;biological sex&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;phenotypic sex&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Preference">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Discrimination"/>
    <obo:IAO_000_0412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000773"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Präferenz</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">preference</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Preference quality involves a liking or inclination toward a perceived stimulus</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'preference' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'discrimination'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Discrimination(x) ← Preference(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;preference&apos; then x is a &apos;discrimination&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;preference&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Pupal">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Maturity"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">pupal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">pupal</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001187"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Pupal maturity quality identifies insects in the chrysalis (cocoon) or post-larval stage</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pupal' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'maturity'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001187.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Maturity(x) ← Pupal(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;pupal&apos; then x is a &apos;maturity&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;pupal&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/PartialTrisomy">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Trisomy"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">partial trisomy</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">teilweise Trisomie</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001390"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Partial trisomy quality refers to the condition where an organism has a partial or extra copy of one or more chromosome segments</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'partial trisomy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'trisomy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001390.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Trisomy(x) ← PartialTrisomy(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;partial trisomy&apos; then x is a &apos;trisomy&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;partial trisomy&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/MaleSterile">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Sterile"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">male sterile</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">männlich steril</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000890"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Male sterile quality indicates the inability of males to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'male sterile' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'sterile'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000890.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Sterile(x) ← MaleSterile(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;male sterile&apos; then x is a &apos;sterile&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;male sterile&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/DeciduousPlant">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Shedability"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">deciduous (plant)</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">laubabwerfende Pflanze</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001731"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Deciduous (plant) is a quality signifying a tendency to shed foliage seasonally</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'deciduous (plant)' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shedability'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001731.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Shedability(x) ← DeciduousPlant(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;deciduous (plant)&apos; then x is a &apos;shedability&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;deciduous (plant)&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Monosomy">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Aneuploid"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">monosomie</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">monosomy</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001386"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Monosomy quality is characterized by the presence of only a single chromosome from a pair within a cell's nucleus</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'monosomy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'aneuploid'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001386.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Aneuploid(x) ← Monosomy(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;monosomy&apos; then x is a &apos;aneuploid&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;monosomy&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Female">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/PhenotypicSex"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">female</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">weiblich</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000383"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Female quality is expressed as the production of gametes capable of being fertilized by male gametes</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'female' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'phenotypic sex'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000383.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">PhenotypicSex(x) ← Female(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;female&apos; then x is a &apos;phenotypic sex&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;female&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/HighNuclear/CytoplasmicRatio">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/CellularQuality"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">hohes nukleär-zytoplasmatisches Verhältnis</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040072"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">High nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio quality defines cells where the nucleus takes up a disproportionate volume compared to the cytoplasm</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'cellular quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040072.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">CellularQuality(x) ← CytoplasmicRatio(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio&apos; then x is a &apos;cellular quality&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/MaleFertility">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/Fertility"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">male fertility</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">männliche Fruchtbarkeit</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000279"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Male fertility quality refers to the male's disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'male fertility' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'fertility'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000279.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Fertility(x) ← MaleFertility(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;male fertility&apos; then x is a &apos;fertility&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;male fertility&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/FemaleFertile">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Biological/FemaleFertility"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">female fertile</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">weiblich fruchtbar</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000888"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Female fertile quality indicates a female's disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'female fertile' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'female fertility'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000888.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">FemaleFertility(x) ← FemaleFertile(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;female fertile&apos; then x is a &apos;female fertility&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;female fertile&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
